The paper deals with the problem of visual polysemy in keyword-based image search, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves dynamically selecting text queries based on image search results, which involves information retrieval techniques (cs.IR). The paper also employs a deep learning network for classification, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for text query selection (cs.CL) and multimedia analysis for image search (cs.MM).
